name: HSBC Net Helpdesk Call Coaching Sheet

questions.text:
Call Opening:

Did the agent answer the call/chat immediately (within 10 seconds) when it was received?
questions.helpText: Agent greeted the customer in a polite manner?

questions.text:
Call Opening:

Was an appropriate welcome/greeting used ?

Call Closing:

Did the agent close the interaction correctly?

Rapport:

What level of rapport did the agent display to engage the customer?

Ownership:

What level of ownership did the agent display?

Ownership:

Did the agent offer a call back / email to the customer? If yes, was the call back made / email sent within promised timelines?

Communication:

How effective was the agent's communication skills?

Service Optimized:

Did the agent discover or identify the customer's primary reason/s for contacting the bank or establish a reason for requesting assistance?

Service optimized:

Did the agent use appropriate trouble-shooting path to identify the issue? Eg did they look at the right screens/systems and ask only relevant questions?

Service Optimized:

Was the customer's reason for calling accurately addressed / Was accurate information provided ? 
Were next steps clearly explained where necessary?

Service Optimized:

Were servicing and value add options explained to the customer (with  focus on self service options) when appropriate? Eg Virtual Assistant, Help Centre, Message Centre

Adherence to internal policies & procedures:

Did the agent follow proper policies and procedures, including appropriate logging in ECHO? And inappropriate disclosure of Internal, Restricted or Highly Restricted information? (Including ID&V performed on the user)* see checklist

Adherence to internal policies & procedures:

Did the agent follow the correct regulation and compliance standards?  Including when a query was not logged as a complaint when it should have been. * see checklist
